wiki.content: "Lie to Girls" is a song by Sabrina Carpenter, from her sixth album, Short n' Sweet. It was written by Sabrina Carpenter, Jack Antonoff and Amy Allen. Both exploring the limits of what a girl does for a man as well as being the most scathing track off the album, “Lie to Girls” is the pinnacle of the vengeful dialogue that Sabrina has towards her ex lover throughout the album. With Sabrina going on to reprimand her lover, that girls lie, cry, and even go insane, in order to date him; but it is also a two way road, where the partner also lies in order to maintain the false pretenses of a relationship. During the tracking week ending on August 29, 2024, “Lie To Girls” debuted at #41 on the Billboard Hot 100. This marks Sabrina’s twelfth highest-debut and her thirteenth highest-peaking song on the chart. Read more on Last.fm.
